<sn><md>Some Important Literary Figures of the Anglo Saxon Period:

:::.row
:::.col-12 .col-md-8
#### Caedmon:

-  He is called the `earliest/first poet` of English literature.
-  Earliest poet / first known poet in English Literature.
-  Comparison: Similar to `Luipa`, the earliest poet of ++Bengali literature++.
- He was a poet of `Christian ideologies`/themes.
- He is also called the `Father of English Sacred Song`.
- Some also refer to him as the `Milton of the Anglo-Saxon Era`.
- His primary literary work is titled `Paraphrase`.
:::

:::.col-12 .col-md-4
![img](https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcTwwIZF73b6UBDTPWr4hZjYwEIrBfO18y0AdUZarTcIlgugdB6LeAMbaqk&amp;s=10)
:::
